<paragraph id="8BA036826A5BC11F11ECF8914267F879" blockId="1.[151,1437,1687,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Body dorsally dark and iridescent, metallic blue or green. Ventrally dark castaneous with metallic green or blue shine; abdomen with three longitudinal reddish bands. Head in front of eyes dark; juga with metallic green shine. Fourth and fifth antennal segments missing. Anterolateral margins of pronotum rugose with a short red stripe not reaching base of humeral angles. Propleura densely punctured. Metasternal process dark brown branches divergent, slightly curved, and evanescent; anterior bifurcation not completely excavated leaving free part of the branches short (
<figureCitation id="13242A076A5BC11F11F7F82D4274F879" box="[222,331,1976,2000]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,638,661]" captionTargetBox="[180,1405,213,616]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,617]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Edessa metallica sp. nov. 1, Female, genital plates. 2 – 3, Metasternal process; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view. (gc 8, gonocoxites 8; gc 9, gonocoxites 9; la 8, laterotergites 8; la 9, laterotergites 9; VII, urotergite VII; X, abdominal segment X. Scale = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Figs. 
<number id="3DD724A56A5BC11F1037F82D4274F879" box="[286,331,1976,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF60660A6A58C11C11BEFDEB420DFD78" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205147/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" targetBox="[180,1405,213,616]" targetPageId="2">
